><head><title>glDepthMask</title><link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" type="text/css"/><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.59.1"/><link rel="home" href="index.xml" title="PyOpenGL 2.0.1.09 Man Pages"/><link rel="up" href="reference-GL.xml" title="GL"/><link rel="previous" href="glDepthFunc.3G.xml" title="glDepthFunc"/><link rel="next" href="glDepthRange.3G.xml" title="glDepthRange"/></head><body bgcolor="white" text="black" link="#0000FF" vlink="#840084" alink="#0000FF"><div class="navheader"><table width="100%" summary="Navigation header"><tr><th colspan="3" align="center">glDepthMask</th></tr><tr><td width="20%" align="left"><a accesskey="p" href="glDepthFunc.3G.xml">Prev</a> </td><th width="60%" align="center">GL</th><td width="20%" align="right"> <a accesskey="n" href="glDepthRange.3G.xml">Next</a></td></tr></table><hr/></div><div class="refentry" lang="en"><a name="glDepthMask.3G"/><div class="titlepage"/><div class="refnamediv"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-name"/><h2>Name</h2><p>glDepthMask &#8212; enable or disable writing into the depth buffer</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-c_spec"/><h2>C Specification</h2><table class="funcprototype" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><code>void <tt>glDepthMask</tt></code></td><td valign="top"><code>(</code></td><td valign="top"><code>GLboolean <i><tt>flag</tt></i>);</code></td></tr></table></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-python_spec"/><h2>Python Specification</h2><table class="funcprototype" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td valign="top"><code><tt>glDepthMask</tt></code></td><td valign="top"><code>(</code></td><td valign="top"><code><i><tt>flag</tt></i>) &#8594; <tt>None</tt></code></td></tr></table></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-parameters"/><h2>Parameters</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl><dt><span class="term"><i><tt>flag</tt></i></span></dt><dd>
						Specifies whether the depth buffer is enabled for writing. If <i><tt>flag</tt></i> is
						<tt>GL_FALSE</tt>, depth buffer writing is disabled. Otherwise, it is enabled. Initially, depth
						buffer writing is enabled.
					</dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-description"/><h2>Description</h2><p>
			<tt>glDepthMask</tt> specifies whether the depth buffer is enabled for writing. If
			<i><tt>flag</tt></i> is <tt>GL_FALSE</tt>, depth buffer writing is disabled. Otherwise, it is
			enabled. Initially, depth buffer writing is enabled.
		</p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-errors"/><h2>Errors</h2><p>
			<tt>GL_INVALID_OPERATION</tt> is generated if <tt>glDepthMask</tt> is executed between the
			execution of <a href="glBegin.3G.xml"><tt>glBegin</tt></a> and the corresponding execution of <a href="glBegin.3G.xml"><tt>glEnd</tt></a>.
		</p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-associated_gets"/><h2>Associated Gets</h2><p>
			<tt>glGet</tt> with argument <tt>GL_DEPTH_WRITEMASK</tt>
		</p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en"><a name="glDepthMask.3G-see_also"/><h2>See Also</h2><p>
